===2000 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=January 31, 2008|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 1,209 people, 424 households, and 339 families residing in the village. The population density was {{convert|4,752.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 447 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,757.0|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial & ethnic makeup of the village was 91.89% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.66% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 4.96% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 1.32% from [[Race (United States Census)|other ethnicities and/or ethnic groups]], and 1.16% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 3.97% of the population.

There were 424 households, out of which 38.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 74.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 4.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 20.0% were non-families. 18.9% of all households were made up of individuals, and 16.5% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.85 and the average family size was 3.27.

In the village, the population was spread out, with 27.2% under the age of 18, 4.9% from 18 to 24, 18.4% from 25 to 44, 28.4% from 45 to 64, and 21.1% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 45 years. For every 100 females, there were 90.7 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 84.9 males.

The median income for a household in the village was $115,916, and the median income for a family was $133,235. Males had a median income of $100,000 versus $62,500 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the village was $59,183. About 0.9% of families and 1.2% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 1.5% of those under age 18 and none of those age 65 or over.

As per the [[United States 2000 Census]], Kensington had the highest percentage of [[Israeli American]] residents among all communities in the United States, at 6.2%.<ref>[http://www.epodunk.com/ancestry/Israeli.html Israeli Ancestry] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071107090628/http://www.epodunk.com/ancestry/Israeli.html |date=November 7, 2007 }}.  Retrieved on July 22, 2014.</ref>

